			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I know this has been brought up before, but I can't recall ever seeing any real logic- why is the cap for our mez so much lower than that for Necromancers?
<br />

<br />
Has there ever been anything stated in regard to this?
<br />

<br />
I know it's a minor issue since our mez is only useful in Takish LDoN for the most part, with limited usefulness in BoT, but it's annoying as hell to be doing Normal LDoN runs and get the 'target is too high to mez' message.
<br />

<br />
Necro I was grouped with in Takish commented on it last night, wondered the same, why is ours capped so low.
<br />

<br />
I don't want to turn this into a rant- I am just curious as to whether this was an oversight that was never fixed (ours too low, or Necro cap too high), or intentional.
<br />

<br />
Given the number of summoned mobs in game I can't imagine the discrepancy was intended- it's not like it would change game balance.
<br />

<br />
Has Brenlo ever commented on this?  I don't recall ever seeing any 'official' reasoning.
<br />

<br />
It's a minor thing that most could care less about, I'm sure, but pertinent to those few of us who still enjoy doing LDoN.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
