				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Balance rarely includes adding abilities</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
I'm not the one who added a MEZ and CHARM to the Magician class, they did that on their own.  I'm just asking it be made a bit more useful, similar to what necros have for their mez (level 65 mobs).
<br />

<br />
Enchanters and Bards can mez up to level 68, any mob.
<br />
Necros can charm undeads up to level 65. 
<br />
Mages get summoned only mobs, up to level 60.
<br />

<br />
A level 65 (soon to be 70!) magician won't find very many uses for the spell. 
<br />

<br />
Remove the mez and charm spells and give us something better to balance us.<br />_________________<br /><DIV *****"position:relative; width=80%; filter:glow(color=FF0000)"><a *****"font-weight:bold; color:#FFFFFF; text-decoration: none" href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4796  target="new-window"><b>Master Zacatac Soulwanderer</b></a></div>"1450 Club" Tradeskiller</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
